{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/kubernetes/docs/flannel/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Setting up Flannel on Kubernetes","date":"November 15, 2024"},"html":"<h1>Kubernetes Cluster 설정을 위한 커맨드</h1>\n<ol>\n<li>Install docker</li>\n</ol>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">sudo su\napt-get update\napt-get install apt-transport-https\napt install docker.io -y\ndocker --version\nsystemctl start docker\nsystemctl enable docker\n</code></pre>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>Install kubernetes</li>\n</ol>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">echo \"deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg] https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/v1.28/deb/ /\" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/kubernetes.list\ncurl -fsSL https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/v1.28/deb/Release.key | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg\nsudo apt update\nsudo apt install -y kubelet kubeadm kubectl kubernetes-cni\n</code></pre>\n<ol start=\"3\">\n<li>Initialize kubernetes cluster on master node</li>\n</ol>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">sudo kubeadm init \n</code></pre>\n<ol start=\"4\">\n<li>Install flannel network</li>\n</ol>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">mkdir -p $HOME/.kube\ncp -i /etc/kubernetes/admin.conf $HOME/.kube/config\nchown $(id -u):$(id -g) $HOME/.kube/config\nkubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/coreos/flannel/master/Documentation/kube-flannel.yml\n\nkubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/flannel-io/flannel/v0.22.2/Documentation/k8s-old-manifests/kube-flannel-rbac.yml \n</code></pre>\n<ol start=\"5\">\n<li>Join worker nodes to the cluster</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Something like this will have popped up after running <code>kubeadm init</code> on the master node. Input it in each worker node.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">kubeadm join 172.31.6.173:6443 --token skfdqw.npr6kjhyir2brmbl \\\n\t--discovery-token-ca-cert-hash sha256:56099fb568309840b7ee3df9895e54e4c95e89a5a88984e7821dfa4905e97348\n</code></pre>\n<p>Once that is done, the nodes will appear as ready as below:<br>\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 31.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"3\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/4fbf56c5b5daf4b06fe865f035c50b29/5a190/readynodes.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4fbf56c5b5daf4b06fe865f035c50b29/772e8/readynodes.png 200w,\n/static/4fbf56c5b5daf4b06fe865f035c50b29/e17e5/readynodes.png 400w,\n/static/4fbf56c5b5daf4b06fe865f035c50b29/5a190/readynodes.png 800w,\n/static/4fbf56c5b5daf4b06fe865f035c50b29/c1b63/readynodes.png 1200w,\n/static/4fbf56c5b5daf4b06fe865f035c50b29/29007/readynodes.png 1600w,\n/static/4fbf56c5b5daf4b06fe865f035c50b29/1105b/readynodes.png 2940w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<ol start=\"6\">\n<li>Create a deployment</li>\n</ol>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">kubectl create deployment nginx --image=nginx --replicas=2\n</code></pre>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 67.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"4\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/f5144fe8d40e30a287a23f17ea3d7a93/5a190/createdeployment.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f5144fe8d40e30a287a23f17ea3d7a93/772e8/createdeployment.png 200w,\n/static/f5144fe8d40e30a287a23f17ea3d7a93/e17e5/createdeployment.png 400w,\n/static/f5144fe8d40e30a287a23f17ea3d7a93/5a190/createdeployment.png 800w,\n/static/f5144fe8d40e30a287a23f17ea3d7a93/c1b63/createdeployment.png 1200w,\n/static/f5144fe8d40e30a287a23f17ea3d7a93/29007/createdeployment.png 1600w,\n/static/f5144fe8d40e30a287a23f17ea3d7a93/966c1/createdeployment.png 1694w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<ol start=\"7\">\n<li>Add <code>/run/flannel/subnet.env</code> file to each node</li>\n</ol>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">echo \"FLANNEL_NETWORK=10.244.0.0/16\nFLANNEL_SUBNET=10.244.0.1/24\nFLANNEL_MTU=1450\nFLANNEL_IPMASQ=true\" > tmp\nsudo mv tmp /run/flannel/subnet.env\n</code></pre>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"flannelwork\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/ad97fd7cfb4636e648e0a12309d098f9/5a190/flannelworking.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ad97fd7cfb4636e648e0a12309d098f9/772e8/flannelworking.png 200w,\n/static/ad97fd7cfb4636e648e0a12309d098f9/e17e5/flannelworking.png 400w,\n/static/ad97fd7cfb4636e648e0a12309d098f9/5a190/flannelworking.png 800w,\n/static/ad97fd7cfb4636e648e0a12309d098f9/c1b63/flannelworking.png 1200w,\n/static/ad97fd7cfb4636e648e0a12309d098f9/29007/flannelworking.png 1600w,\n/static/ad97fd7cfb4636e648e0a12309d098f9/1105b/flannelworking.png 2940w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span>\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 31.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"flannelwork\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/5e3c0f38c9b43d1cf4c0b0718f376e83/5a190/flannelworking2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5e3c0f38c9b43d1cf4c0b0718f376e83/772e8/flannelworking2.png 200w,\n/static/5e3c0f38c9b43d1cf4c0b0718f376e83/e17e5/flannelworking2.png 400w,\n/static/5e3c0f38c9b43d1cf4c0b0718f376e83/5a190/flannelworking2.png 800w,\n/static/5e3c0f38c9b43d1cf4c0b0718f376e83/c1b63/flannelworking2.png 1200w,\n/static/5e3c0f38c9b43d1cf4c0b0718f376e83/c4451/flannelworking2.png 1450w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h1>References</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://cloudzenia.com/blog/a-beginners-guide-to-deploying-a-kubernetes-cluster-on-ec2-instances-with-kubeadm/\">A Beginner’s Guide to Deploying a Kubernetes Cluster on EC2 Instances with Kubeadm</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/123673\">Installing kubernetes on Ubuntu</a></li>\n</ul>"}},